a poem i got when my dog died hey there i got this poem from my gran when my dog died a loss of a companion if it should be that i grow weak and pain should keep me from my sleep then you must do what must be done for this last battle can't be won you will be sad i understand don't let your grief then stay your hand for this day more than all the rest your love for me must stand the test we've had so may happy years what is to come can hold no fears you'd not want me to suffer so the time has come please let me go take me to where my needs they'll tend and please stay with me till the end hold me firm and speak to me until my eyes no longer see please do not grieve it must be you who has this painful thing to do wev'e been so close we two these years don't let your heart hold back the tears i just wanted to share that poem with you al r was i just sharing a poem i got when my dog died what was the point of that answer thank you so much for taking the time to type it up and share it with everyone on here it is a truly beautiful and touching poem i cried i am printing it out to bring into work with me so many of our clients are so blind when it comes to seeing that their dog does not have a quality of life anymore almost as if they are in denial i am thinking of one of our clients in particular who has canceled and rescheduled the euthanasia for their dog for the last weeks the poor old boy is suffering and has that look in his eyes like please let me go it breaks my heart i am going to share the poem with her thanks again Jon Secada Billboard Hot 100 Shaggy dog story Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Grief Cindy Sheehan Dean Koontz EastEnders Pitaten Kodocha Time Out of Mind Parsifal Past teachings of Prem Rawat The Amber Spyglass Miss Saigon American Psycho Night (book) Scenes from a Memory W.I.T.C.H. One Tree Hill (TV series) Theodicy Three Stooges Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Zhao Yun Fitz Hugh Ludlow Reaction to the assassination of John F. K